  <data name="lblTOS.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>InnoBridge - Privacy Policy
Effective Date: July 10, 2025

1. Introduction
InnoBridge respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard your data.

2. Information We Collect
We may collect the following information during registration and platform usage:
- Full name
- Email address
- Username (optional)
- Date of Birth
- User type (Student or Organization)

3. How We Use Your Information
Your information is used solely for the purpose of:
- Creating and managing user accounts
- Connecting students with industry projects
- Enabling collaboration between users
- Improving platform functionality

4. Data Sharing
InnoBridge does not sell or share your data with third parties. However, submitted project content may be publicly visible on the platform for collaboration purposes.

5. Data Security
We use basic security measures to protect your data. However, please note that this is a student-built project and we cannot guarantee full commercial-grade protection.

6. Your Rights
You have the right to:
- View or edit your profile
- Request account deletion
- Contact us for any concerns related to your data

7. Cookies and Tracking
InnoBridge does not use cookies or advanced tracking technologies. All interactions occur within the application interface only.

8. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect improvements or feedback. Continued use of the platform implies acceptance of the updated terms.

9. Contact
If you have questions regarding your privacy or data, please contact us at innobridge@email.com.

By using this platform, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy.</value>
